projects:
[{'title': 'Stratos II+ Sounding Rocket (Lead Propulsion Engineer)', 'date': {'start': {'month': 6, 'day': None, 'year': 2010}, 'end': {'month': 10, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}}, 'description': 'During the development phase of the propulsion segment for the Stratos II+ sounding rocket I was leading a team of 8 students, that by themselves designed, built, and tested the 10 kN hybrid rocket motor DHX-200 Aurora powering the Stratos II+ rocket on its record-breaking flight in October 2015.

The propulsion segment consists of a 200,000 Ns hybrid rocket motor as well as all support equipment, all of which has been developed purely by students at Delft Aerospace Rocket Engineering. Stratos II+ was launched in October 2015 to an altitude of 21.5 km transporting scientific payloads with it and breaking the European altitude record for amateur rocket vehicles.
